deck: Alien from the planet Elysia, and last descendant of the Earth super-villain Dr. Ex-Mortis
description:
Mortius is an alien/human hybrid from the planet Elysia. He looks like an orange and white colored cat-man with almost black mustache, goatee, and long hair. He is the last descendant of the 70s-era super-villain Dr. Phineas J. Ex-Mortis.

He was transported to Earth along with his enemy Lana by a device constructed by his ancestor Dr. Ex-Mortis. He escaped capture and fled to Fortress Kia, which he took over. Upon initial exposure to the Internet, he was easily distracted from his evil plans by various online games. With the help of Gina, Britanny, Avenger, and Agency Zero, Lana pursued him and managed to capture him.

Like all descendants of Ex-Mortis, Mortius possesses nanomachines in his blood called Doll-Ex. These nanomachines allow him to reconstruct the matter of any small simple item into a tech-weapon or tech-tool. These nanomachines also drive him to pursue the same degree of evil mad science as the original Dr. Ex-Mortis.
name: Mortius

deck: Priestess from the planet Elysia, and enemy of the descendants of Dr. Ex-Mortis
description:
Lana is an alien who looks like a lavender and white colored cat-girl. She is a priestess from the planet Elysia. She tends to become embarrassed when talking about her abilities around males and can be distracted by well-endowed males. Her people have been fighting the descendants of Dr. Phineas J. Ex-Mortis for 1000 years.

She was transported to Earth along with Mortius, the last descendant of Dr. Ex-Mortis. With the help of Gina, Britanny, Avenger, and Agency Zero, she has finally defeated Mortius. She is currently stuck on Earth since it will take Gina about 5 years to finish the math needed to open a path home. Both Gina and Agency Zero are looking for a better solution. In the mean time, she is helping Agency Zero.

Lana channels all of her magic through her Anahata chakra (her cleavage). This makes all of her attacks spectral in nature, which is difficult for technology to deflect. As a side effect, her breasts grow and shrink somewhat depending on her mana levels.
name: Lana

deck: One of the War Boys who betrayed Immortan Joe. He worked alongside Imperator Furiosa and Mad Max during the battle along Fury Road.
description:
Origin

Nux's parents were citizens in the Citadel; however, their names were unknown. Nux's father was killed after being recruited for a mission outside of the Citadel that ran into a hostile raider party, but Nux was so young he couldn't comprehend his death. Nux, believing his father to still be alive, attempted to find him by clinging to the elevator in the Citadel.

he elevator guardians wanted to test him to see how strong he was, they tried knocking him off but young Nux prove he was a tough nut to crack. Astonished at his strength and endurance at such a young age Nux became a member of Immortan Joe's War Boys.

Creation

Nux was created by George Miller for the 2015 film Mad Max: Fury Road.

Character Evolution

Nux was originally a follower of Immortan Joe and was willing to die for his cause, attempting to impress him on several occasions. When Nux failed in front of Joe he suffered a great amount of shame and abandoned his cause as he saw no more purpose in trying.

Nux was found on the war-rig by one of Immortan Joe's wives and was taken in, eventually becoming a vital member of Furiosa's team. While Nux's life outside of the War Boys was short lived he had finally learned to become his own person and discovered a purpose in his life.

Major Story Arcs

Fury Road

When Furiosa betrayed Immortan Joe the War Boys were called to chase her, young Nux was one of the many who attempted to bring her back to the Citadel. It was during this chase that Nux met Mad Max, who was Nux's blood bag (a living blood supply) and was strapped to the front of Nux's vehicle. Nux ended up getting in an accident after Max broke free from his restraints and attacked Nux.

Surviving the accident Nux was attached to Max via handcuffs, Max woke up before Nux and carried him through the wasteland, following the tracks of the war-rig. Nux woke up as Max was fighting with Furiosa, believing that Max was attempting to capture her Nux joined the fight; however, he was incorrect in his assumptions. Max was able to cut the link between himself and Nux and left Nux in the wasteland while he and Furiosa drove away in the war-rig.

Nux was picked up by Immortan Joe and the War Boys and informed Joe of the path the war-rig was taking. Such an act gained him a seat in Immortan Joe's vehicle as the pursuit continued. When they met up with the war-rig Nux tried to mount an assault on the vehicle; however, he failed and was disowned by Immortan Joe. Due to the great shame this caused him he decided to hide on the war-rig and wait for death to greet him.

While on the rig he was discovered by one of Immortan Joe's wives. She was able to help ease his pain and reassured him that there are greater things in life than impression Immortan Joe. Viewing life with a renewed purpose Nux decided to work alongside Furiosa and Mad Max, helping them fight off the War Boys while repairing the war-rig in battle.

Nux made the ultimate sacrifice when they were headed back to the Citadel, as the driver of the war-rig he crashed it to prevent the War Boys from reaching Furiosa and Max. Nux was killed in the resulting explosion of the crash but died knowing he was a hero.

Skills & Abilities

Nux was shown to be a skilled mechanic and had above-average skills in vehicular combat.

In Other Media

Mad Max: Fury Road

In the 2015 film Mad Max: Fury Road Nux was portrayed by Nicholas Hoult.
name: Nux

deck: Jarvis and Jeeves are Ayane Anno's 2 personal servants in the Gold Digger universe.
description:
Jarvis and Jeeves are the 2 personal servants for Ayane Anno in the Gold Digger universe. They both appear to be extremely handsome men with shoulder length wavy hair and blue eyes. Jarvis has brown skin and white hair, while Jeeves has pale skin and black hair. It has been shown that they are in fact Amonian "environment shells", artificial bodies designed for environments too hazardous for an Amonian's normal body and into which a mind can be copied.

It is unknown how long the two have been active, but they have been taking care of Ayane for as long as she can recall and have not visibly aged during that time. They and Monty have been both hiding and protecting Ayane's true nature as one of the last full Amonians from herself and the world. They also help with Ayane's UFF persona as Mistress; during all such public appearances, they always wear symmetrically mirrored masks to hide their attractiveness so as not to distract from Ayane herself.
name: Jarvis

Dee'em is a Dwemeor (dwarf) arch-mage and architect within the the Gold Digger universe. He is a geek culture reference to the character Dungeon Master from the Dungeon & Dragons cartoon.

Dee'em has been around at least since the end of the Age of Magic when he and other dwemeor artisans built the world's largest golem, Labyrinth. In modern times, he was in Seer's Hamlet where he consulted on Brianna's hybrid condition with other arch-mages. Later on, he helped guide Gina's group through the golem Labyrinth to reach the super-weapon Gigliathon and attempt to remove its beta-technology Giga Engine.

Origin

Maya Ducard is the daughter of the original Nobody (Morgan Ducard) and Felicity Strode. After her father died at the hands of Damian Wayne (Robin), she swore revenge on him. She modified Nobody's suit and set out to kill him. However, she soon developed a friendship with him. Together, they fight crime and evil wherever they encounter it.

Powers and Abilities

Skilled in unarmed combat and armed combat

Stealth/Invisibility (due to cloaking device)

Tracking

Sonic Devices in her suit

Variety of gadgets contained in her suit

Maya's suit contains an array of gadgetry and weaponry that she utilizes to fight crime. One of these is a cloaking device much like the one Nobody uses, which allows her to move unseen and undetected. Her suit also has sonic devices which emit varying frequencies of sound to knock out enemies.

deck: Zealot from Necromunda
description:
Klovis of House Cawdor is a fanatical, psychopathic priest from the Redemptionist doctrine in the Hive World of Necromunda. The Redemptionists are considered lunatic zealots even by the most hardcore followers of the mainstream Imperial faith, which even in its normal form is fundamentalist death cult. The name comes from the belief that one can only be redeemed of sin in death, and that very nearly everything is a sin. The standard Imperial faith focus their hatred on witches, mutants and aliens. But for Redemptionists, sin exists in every creature, which can be purged only through bloodshed. They are considered so radical that they are officially banned in some worlds, put in the same bracket as heretics. A testament to how vile they are that even the highly xenophobic, fundamentalistic Imperials consider them to pose as much as a threat than many outsider enemies.

Necromunda is the homeworld of the Redemption doctrine, which is considered the official religion through House Cawdor's influence. Klovis is the most notorious Redemptionist in the whole planet fighting against hordes of heretics and aliens, purging both the unfaithful and the pious, leaving the God-Emperor of Mankind know who is his own. He is absolutely merciless to all around him, not even his own men are safe from his wrath - going as far as to eviscerate one of his followers for not keeping his own equipament clean. He takes absolute delight in torturing and murdering, with his battle cry being "SCOURGE AND PURGE".
name: The Redeemer
